72  class ASTStmtReader : public StmtVisitor<ASTStmtReader> {
73  ASTRecordReader &Record;
74  llvm::BitstreamCursor &DeclsCursor;
75 
76  std::optional<BitsUnpacker> CurrentUnpackingBits;
77 
78  SourceLocation readSourceLocation() {
79  return Record.readSourceLocation();
80  }
81 
82  SourceRange readSourceRange() {
83  return Record.readSourceRange();
84  }
85 
86  std::string readString() {
87  return Record.readString();
88  }
89 
90  TypeSourceInfo *readTypeSourceInfo() {
91  return Record.readTypeSourceInfo();
92  }
93 
94  Decl *readDecl() {
95  return Record.readDecl();
96  }
97 
98  template<typename T>
99  T *readDeclAs() {
100  return Record.readDeclAs<T>();
101  }
102 
103  public:
104  ASTStmtReader(ASTRecordReader &Record, llvm::BitstreamCursor &Cursor)
105  : Record(Record), DeclsCursor(Cursor) {}
106 
107  /// The number of record fields required for the Stmt class
108  /// itself.
109  static const unsigned NumStmtFields = 0;
110 
111  /// The number of record fields required for the Expr class
112  /// itself.
113  static const unsigned NumExprFields = NumStmtFields + 2;
114 
115  /// The number of bits required for the packing bits for the Expr class.
116  static const unsigned NumExprBits = 10;
117 
118  /// Read and initialize a ExplicitTemplateArgumentList structure.
119  void ReadTemplateKWAndArgsInfo(ASTTemplateKWAndArgsInfo &Args,
120  TemplateArgumentLoc *ArgsLocArray,
121  unsigned NumTemplateArgs);
122 
123  void VisitStmt(Stmt *S);
124 #define STMT(Type, Base) \
125  void Visit##Type(Type *);
126 #include "clang/AST/StmtNodes.inc"
127  };
128 
129 } // namespace clang

131 void ASTStmtReader::ReadTemplateKWAndArgsInfo(ASTTemplateKWAndArgsInfo &Args,
132  TemplateArgumentLoc *ArgsLocArray,
133  unsigned NumTemplateArgs) {
134  SourceLocation TemplateKWLoc = readSourceLocation();
135  TemplateArgumentListInfo ArgInfo;
136  ArgInfo.setLAngleLoc(readSourceLocation());
137  ArgInfo.setRAngleLoc(readSourceLocation());
138  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumTemplateArgs; ++i)
139  ArgInfo.addArgument(Record.readTemplateArgumentLoc());
140  Args.initializeFrom(TemplateKWLoc, ArgInfo, ArgsLocArray);
141 }

153 void ASTStmtReader::VisitCompoundStmt(CompoundStmt *S) {
154  VisitStmt(S);
155  SmallVector<Stmt *, 16> Stmts;
156  unsigned NumStmts = Record.readInt();
157  unsigned HasFPFeatures = Record.readInt();
158  assert(S->hasStoredFPFeatures() == HasFPFeatures);
159  while (NumStmts--)
160  Stmts.push_back(Record.readSubStmt());
161  S->setStmts(Stmts);
162  if (HasFPFeatures)
163  S->setStoredFPFeatures(
164  FPOptionsOverride::getFromOpaqueInt(Record.readInt()));
165  S->LBraceLoc = readSourceLocation();
166  S->RBraceLoc = readSourceLocation();
167 }

169 void ASTStmtReader::VisitSwitchCase(SwitchCase *S) {
170  VisitStmt(S);
171  Record.recordSwitchCaseID(S, Record.readInt());
172  S->setKeywordLoc(readSourceLocation());
173  S->setColonLoc(readSourceLocation());
174 }

176 void ASTStmtReader::VisitCaseStmt(CaseStmt *S) {
177  VisitSwitchCase(S);
178  bool CaseStmtIsGNURange = Record.readInt();
179  S->setLHS(Record.readSubExpr());
180  S->setSubStmt(Record.readSubStmt());
181  if (CaseStmtIsGNURange) {
182  S->setRHS(Record.readSubExpr());
183  S->setEllipsisLoc(readSourceLocation());
184  }
185 }

192 void ASTStmtReader::VisitLabelStmt(LabelStmt *S) {
193  VisitStmt(S);
194  bool IsSideEntry = Record.readInt();
195  auto *LD = readDeclAs<LabelDecl>();
196  LD->setStmt(S);
197  S->setDecl(LD);
198  S->setSubStmt(Record.readSubStmt());
199  S->setIdentLoc(readSourceLocation());
200  S->setSideEntry(IsSideEntry);

203 void ASTStmtReader::VisitAttributedStmt(AttributedStmt *S) {
204  VisitStmt(S);
205  // NumAttrs in AttributedStmt is set when creating an empty
206  // AttributedStmt in AttributedStmt::CreateEmpty, since it is needed
207  // to allocate the right amount of space for the trailing Attr *.
208  uint64_t NumAttrs = Record.readInt();
209  AttrVec Attrs;
210  Record.readAttributes(Attrs);
211  (void)NumAttrs;
212  assert(NumAttrs == S->AttributedStmtBits.NumAttrs);
213  assert(NumAttrs == Attrs.size());
214  std::copy(Attrs.begin(), Attrs.end(), S->getAttrArrayPtr());
215  S->SubStmt = Record.readSubStmt();
216  S->AttributedStmtBits.AttrLoc = readSourceLocation();
217 }

219 void ASTStmtReader::VisitIfStmt(IfStmt *S) {
220  VisitStmt(S);
221 
222  CurrentUnpackingBits.emplace(Record.readInt());
223 
224  bool HasElse = CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit();
225  bool HasVar = CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit();
226  bool HasInit = CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit();
227 
228  S->setStatementKind(static_cast<IfStatementKind>(Record.readInt()));
229  S->setCond(Record.readSubExpr());
230  S->setThen(Record.readSubStmt());
231  if (HasElse)
232  S->setElse(Record.readSubStmt());
233  if (HasVar)
234  S->setConditionVariableDeclStmt(cast<DeclStmt>(Record.readSubStmt()));
235  if (HasInit)
236  S->setInit(Record.readSubStmt());
237 
238  S->setIfLoc(readSourceLocation());
239  S->setLParenLoc(readSourceLocation());
240  S->setRParenLoc(readSourceLocation());
241  if (HasElse)
242  S->setElseLoc(readSourceLocation());
243 }
244 
245 void ASTStmtReader::VisitSwitchStmt(SwitchStmt *S) {
246  VisitStmt(S);
247 
248  bool HasInit = Record.readInt();
249  bool HasVar = Record.readInt();
250  bool AllEnumCasesCovered = Record.readInt();
251  if (AllEnumCasesCovered)
252  S->setAllEnumCasesCovered();
253 
254  S->setCond(Record.readSubExpr());
255  S->setBody(Record.readSubStmt());
256  if (HasInit)
257  S->setInit(Record.readSubStmt());
258  if (HasVar)
259  S->setConditionVariableDeclStmt(cast<DeclStmt>(Record.readSubStmt()));
260 
261  S->setSwitchLoc(readSourceLocation());
262  S->setLParenLoc(readSourceLocation());
263  S->setRParenLoc(readSourceLocation());
264 
265  SwitchCase *PrevSC = nullptr;
266  for (auto E = Record.size(); Record.getIdx() != E; ) {
267  SwitchCase *SC = Record.getSwitchCaseWithID(Record.readInt());
268  if (PrevSC)
269  PrevSC->setNextSwitchCase(SC);
270  else
271  S->setSwitchCaseList(SC);
272 
273  PrevSC = SC;
274  }
275 }

286

288  S->setLParenLoc(readSourceLocation());
289  S->setRParenLoc(readSourceLocation());
290 }

337 void ASTStmtReader::VisitReturnStmt(ReturnStmt *S) {
338  VisitStmt(S);
339 
340  bool HasNRVOCandidate = Record.readInt();
341 
342  S->setRetValue(Record.readSubExpr());

349 void ASTStmtReader::VisitDeclStmt(DeclStmt *S) {
350  VisitStmt(S);
351  S->setStartLoc(readSourceLocation());
352  S->setEndLoc(readSourceLocation());
353 
354  if (Record.size() - Record.getIdx() == 1) {
355  // Single declaration
356  S->setDeclGroup(DeclGroupRef(readDecl()));
357  } else {
358  SmallVector<Decl *, 16> Decls;
359  int N = Record.size() - Record.getIdx();
360  Decls.reserve(N);
361  for (int I = 0; I < N; ++I)
362  Decls.push_back(readDecl());
363  S->setDeclGroup(DeclGroupRef(DeclGroup::Create(Record.getContext(),
364  Decls.data(),
365  Decls.size())));
366  }
367 }

369 void ASTStmtReader::VisitAsmStmt(AsmStmt *S) {
370  VisitStmt(S);
371  S->NumOutputs = Record.readInt();
372  S->NumInputs = Record.readInt();
373  S->NumClobbers = Record.readInt();
374  S->setAsmLoc(readSourceLocation());
375  S->setVolatile(Record.readInt());
376  S->setSimple(Record.readInt());
377 }

379 void ASTStmtReader::VisitGCCAsmStmt(GCCAsmStmt *S) {
380  VisitAsmStmt(S);
381  S->NumLabels = Record.readInt();
382  S->setRParenLoc(readSourceLocation());
383  S->setAsmString(cast_or_null<StringLiteral>(Record.readSubStmt()));
384 
385  unsigned NumOutputs = S->getNumOutputs();
386  unsigned NumInputs = S->getNumInputs();
387  unsigned NumClobbers = S->getNumClobbers();
388  unsigned NumLabels = S->getNumLabels();
389 
390  // Outputs and inputs
391  SmallVector<IdentifierInfo *, 16> Names;
392  SmallVector<StringLiteral*, 16> Constraints;
393  SmallVector<Stmt*, 16> Exprs;
394  for (unsigned I = 0, N = NumOutputs + NumInputs; I != N; ++I) {
395  Names.push_back(Record.readIdentifier());
396  Constraints.push_back(cast_or_null<StringLiteral>(Record.readSubStmt()));
397  Exprs.push_back(Record.readSubStmt());
398  }
399 
400  // Constraints
401  SmallVector<StringLiteral*, 16> Clobbers;
402  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumClobbers; ++I)
403  Clobbers.push_back(cast_or_null<StringLiteral>(Record.readSubStmt()));
404 
405  // Labels
406  for (unsigned I = 0, N = NumLabels; I != N; ++I) {
407  Names.push_back(Record.readIdentifier());
408  Exprs.push_back(Record.readSubStmt());
409  }
410 
411  S->setOutputsAndInputsAndClobbers(Record.getContext(),
412  Names.data(), Constraints.data(),
413  Exprs.data(), NumOutputs, NumInputs,
414  NumLabels,
415  Clobbers.data(), NumClobbers);
416 }

418 void ASTStmtReader::VisitMSAsmStmt(MSAsmStmt *S) {
419  VisitAsmStmt(S);
420  S->LBraceLoc = readSourceLocation();
421  S->EndLoc = readSourceLocation();
422  S->NumAsmToks = Record.readInt();
423  std::string AsmStr = readString();
424 
425  // Read the tokens.
426  SmallVector<Token, 16> AsmToks;
427  AsmToks.reserve(S->NumAsmToks);
428  for (unsigned i = 0, e = S->NumAsmToks; i != e; ++i) {
429  AsmToks.push_back(Record.readToken());
430  }
431 
432  // The calls to reserve() for the FooData vectors are mandatory to
433  // prevent dead StringRefs in the Foo vectors.
434 
435  // Read the clobbers.
436  SmallVector<std::string, 16> ClobbersData;
437  SmallVector<StringRef, 16> Clobbers;
438  ClobbersData.reserve(S->NumClobbers);
439  Clobbers.reserve(S->NumClobbers);
440  for (unsigned i = 0, e = S->NumClobbers; i != e; ++i) {
441  ClobbersData.push_back(readString());
442  Clobbers.push_back(ClobbersData.back());
443  }
444 
445  // Read the operands.
446  unsigned NumOperands = S->NumOutputs + S->NumInputs;
447  SmallVector<Expr*, 16> Exprs;
448  SmallVector<std::string, 16> ConstraintsData;
449  SmallVector<StringRef, 16> Constraints;
450  Exprs.reserve(NumOperands);
451  ConstraintsData.reserve(NumOperands);
452  Constraints.reserve(NumOperands);
453  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumOperands; ++i) {
454  Exprs.push_back(cast<Expr>(Record.readSubStmt()));
455  ConstraintsData.push_back(readString());
456  Constraints.push_back(ConstraintsData.back());
457  }
458 
459  S->initialize(Record.getContext(), AsmStr, AsmToks,
460  Constraints, Exprs, Clobbers);
461 }

463 void ASTStmtReader::VisitCoroutineBodyStmt(CoroutineBodyStmt *S) {
464  VisitStmt(S);
465  assert(Record.peekInt() == S->NumParams);
466  Record.skipInts(1);
467  auto *StoredStmts = S->getStoredStmts();
468  for (unsigned i = 0;
469  i < CoroutineBodyStmt::SubStmt::FirstParamMove + S->NumParams; ++i)
470  StoredStmts[i] = Record.readSubStmt();
471 }

505 void ASTStmtReader::VisitCapturedStmt(CapturedStmt *S) {
506  VisitStmt(S);
507  Record.skipInts(1);
508  S->setCapturedDecl(readDeclAs<CapturedDecl>());
509  S->setCapturedRegionKind(static_cast<CapturedRegionKind>(Record.readInt()));
510  S->setCapturedRecordDecl(readDeclAs<RecordDecl>());
511 
512  // Capture inits
513  for (CapturedStmt::capture_init_iterator I = S->capture_init_begin(),
514  E = S->capture_init_end();
515  I != E; ++I)
516  *I = Record.readSubExpr();
517 
518  // Body
519  S->setCapturedStmt(Record.readSubStmt());
520  S->getCapturedDecl()->setBody(S->getCapturedStmt());
521 
522  // Captures
523  for (auto &I : S->captures()) {
524  I.VarAndKind.setPointer(readDeclAs<VarDecl>());
525  I.VarAndKind.setInt(
526  static_cast<CapturedStmt::VariableCaptureKind>(Record.readInt()));
527  I.Loc = readSourceLocation();
528  }
529 }

531 void ASTStmtReader::VisitExpr(Expr *E) {
532  VisitStmt(E);
533  CurrentUnpackingBits.emplace(Record.readInt());
534  E->setDependence(static_cast<ExprDependence>(
535  CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBits(/*Width=*/5)));
536  E->setValueKind(static_cast<ExprValueKind>(
537  CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBits(/*Width=*/2)));
538  E->setObjectKind(static_cast<ExprObjectKind>(
539  CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBits(/*Width=*/3)));
540 
541  E->setType(Record.readType());
542  assert(Record.getIdx() == NumExprFields &&
543  "Incorrect expression field count");
544 }
545 
546 void ASTStmtReader::VisitConstantExpr(ConstantExpr *E) {
547  VisitExpr(E);
548 
549  auto StorageKind = static_cast<ConstantResultStorageKind>(Record.readInt());
550  assert(E->getResultStorageKind() == StorageKind && "Wrong ResultKind!");
551 
552  E->ConstantExprBits.APValueKind = Record.readInt();
553  E->ConstantExprBits.IsUnsigned = Record.readInt();
554  E->ConstantExprBits.BitWidth = Record.readInt();
555  E->ConstantExprBits.HasCleanup = false; // Not serialized, see below.
556  E->ConstantExprBits.IsImmediateInvocation = Record.readInt();
557 
558  switch (StorageKind) {
559  case ConstantResultStorageKind::None:
560  break;
561 
562  case ConstantResultStorageKind::Int64:
563  E->Int64Result() = Record.readInt();
564  break;
565 
566  case ConstantResultStorageKind::APValue:
567  E->APValueResult() = Record.readAPValue();
568  if (E->APValueResult().needsCleanup()) {
569  E->ConstantExprBits.HasCleanup = true;
570  Record.getContext().addDestruction(&E->APValueResult());
571  }
572  break;
573  }
574 
575  E->setSubExpr(Record.readSubExpr());
576 }

598 void ASTStmtReader::VisitPredefinedExpr(PredefinedExpr *E) {
599  VisitExpr(E);
600  bool HasFunctionName = Record.readInt();
601  E->PredefinedExprBits.HasFunctionName = HasFunctionName;
602  E->PredefinedExprBits.Kind = Record.readInt();
603  E->PredefinedExprBits.IsTransparent = Record.readInt();
604  E->setLocation(readSourceLocation());
605  if (HasFunctionName)

609 void ASTStmtReader::VisitDeclRefExpr(DeclRefExpr *E) {
610  VisitExpr(E);
611 
612  CurrentUnpackingBits.emplace(Record.readInt());
613  E->DeclRefExprBits.HadMultipleCandidates = CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit();
614  E->DeclRefExprBits.RefersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture =
615  CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit();
616  E->DeclRefExprBits.NonOdrUseReason =
617  CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBits(/*Width=*/2);
618  E->DeclRefExprBits.IsImmediateEscalating = CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit();
619  E->DeclRefExprBits.HasFoundDecl = CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit();
620  E->DeclRefExprBits.HasQualifier = CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit();
621  E->DeclRefExprBits.HasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo =
622  CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit();
623  E->DeclRefExprBits.CapturedByCopyInLambdaWithExplicitObjectParameter = false;
624  unsigned NumTemplateArgs = 0;
625  if (E->hasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo())
626  NumTemplateArgs = Record.readInt();
627 
628  if (E->hasQualifier())
629  new (E->getTrailingObjects<NestedNameSpecifierLoc>())
630  NestedNameSpecifierLoc(Record.readNestedNameSpecifierLoc());
631 
632  if (E->hasFoundDecl())
633  *E->getTrailingObjects<NamedDecl *>() = readDeclAs<NamedDecl>();
634 
635  if (E->hasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo())
636  ReadTemplateKWAndArgsInfo(
637  *E->getTrailingObjects<ASTTemplateKWAndArgsInfo>(),
638  E->getTrailingObjects<TemplateArgumentLoc>(), NumTemplateArgs);
639 
640  E->D = readDeclAs<ValueDecl>();
641  E->setLocation(readSourceLocation());
642  E->DNLoc = Record.readDeclarationNameLoc(E->getDecl()->getDeclName());
643 }

672 void ASTStmtReader::VisitStringLiteral(StringLiteral *E) {
673  VisitExpr(E);
674 
675  // NumConcatenated, Length and CharByteWidth are set by the empty
676  // ctor since they are needed to allocate storage for the trailing objects.
677  unsigned NumConcatenated = Record.readInt();
678  unsigned Length = Record.readInt();
679  unsigned CharByteWidth = Record.readInt();
680  assert((NumConcatenated == E->getNumConcatenated()) &&
681  "Wrong number of concatenated tokens!");
682  assert((Length == E->getLength()) && "Wrong Length!");
683  assert((CharByteWidth == E->getCharByteWidth()) && "Wrong character width!");
684  E->StringLiteralBits.Kind = Record.readInt();
685  E->StringLiteralBits.IsPascal = Record.readInt();
686 
687  // The character width is originally computed via mapCharByteWidth.
688  // Check that the deserialized character width is consistant with the result
689  // of calling mapCharByteWidth.
690  assert((CharByteWidth ==
691  StringLiteral::mapCharByteWidth(Record.getContext().getTargetInfo(),
692  E->getKind())) &&
693  "Wrong character width!");
694 
695  // Deserialize the trailing array of SourceLocation.
696  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumConcatenated; ++I)
697  E->setStrTokenLoc(I, readSourceLocation());
698 
699  // Deserialize the trailing array of char holding the string data.
700  char *StrData = E->getStrDataAsChar();
701  for (unsigned I = 0; I < Length * CharByteWidth; ++I)
702  StrData[I] = Record.readInt();
703 }

710 }

729 void ASTStmtReader::VisitUnaryOperator(UnaryOperator *E) {
730  VisitExpr(E);

732  assert(hasFP_Features == E->hasStoredFPFeatures());
733  E->setSubExpr(Record.readSubExpr());

735  (UnaryOperator::Opcode)CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBits(/*Width=*/5));

737  E->setCanOverflow(CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit());

743 void ASTStmtReader::VisitOffsetOfExpr(OffsetOfExpr *E) {
744  VisitExpr(E);
745  assert(E->getNumComponents() == Record.peekInt());
746  Record.skipInts(1);
747  assert(E->getNumExpressions() == Record.peekInt());
748  Record.skipInts(1);
749  E->setOperatorLoc(readSourceLocation());
750  E->setRParenLoc(readSourceLocation());
751  E->setTypeSourceInfo(readTypeSourceInfo());
752  for (unsigned I = 0, N = E->getNumComponents(); I != N; ++I) {
753  auto Kind = static_cast<OffsetOfNode::Kind>(Record.readInt());
754  SourceLocation Start = readSourceLocation();
755  SourceLocation End = readSourceLocation();
756  switch (Kind) {
757  case OffsetOfNode::Array:
758  E->setComponent(I, OffsetOfNode(Start, Record.readInt(), End));
759  break;
760 
761  case OffsetOfNode::Field:
762  E->setComponent(
763  I, OffsetOfNode(Start, readDeclAs<FieldDecl>(), End));
764  break;
765 
766  case OffsetOfNode::Identifier:
767  E->setComponent(
768  I,
769  OffsetOfNode(Start, Record.readIdentifier(), End));
770  break;
771 
772  case OffsetOfNode::Base: {
773  auto *Base = new (Record.getContext()) CXXBaseSpecifier();
774  *Base = Record.readCXXBaseSpecifier();
775  E->setComponent(I, OffsetOfNode(Base));
776  break;
777  }
778  }
779  }
780 
781  for (unsigned I = 0, N = E->getNumExpressions(); I != N; ++I)
782  E->setIndexExpr(I, Record.readSubExpr());
783 }
784 
785 void ASTStmtReader::VisitUnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr(UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr *E) {
786  VisitExpr(E);
787  E->setKind(static_cast<UnaryExprOrTypeTrait>(Record.readInt()));
788  if (Record.peekInt() == 0) {
789  E->setArgument(Record.readSubExpr());
790  Record.skipInts(1);
791  } else {
792  E->setArgument(readTypeSourceInfo());
793  }
794  E->setOperatorLoc(readSourceLocation());
795  E->setRParenLoc(readSourceLocation());
796 }
797 
798 static ConstraintSatisfaction
799 readConstraintSatisfaction(ASTRecordReader &Record) {
800  ConstraintSatisfaction Satisfaction;
801  Satisfaction.IsSatisfied = Record.readInt();
802  Satisfaction.ContainsErrors = Record.readInt();
803  if (!Satisfaction.IsSatisfied) {
804  unsigned NumDetailRecords = Record.readInt();
805  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumDetailRecords; ++i) {
806  Expr *ConstraintExpr = Record.readExpr();
807  if (/* IsDiagnostic */Record.readInt()) {
808  SourceLocation DiagLocation = Record.readSourceLocation();
809  std::string DiagMessage = Record.readString();
810  Satisfaction.Details.emplace_back(
811  ConstraintExpr, new (Record.getContext())
812  ConstraintSatisfaction::SubstitutionDiagnostic{
813  DiagLocation, DiagMessage});
814  } else
815  Satisfaction.Details.emplace_back(ConstraintExpr, Record.readExpr());
816  }
817  }
818  return Satisfaction;
819 }

821 void ASTStmtReader::VisitConceptSpecializationExpr(
822  ConceptSpecializationExpr *E) {
823  VisitExpr(E);
824  E->SpecDecl = Record.readDeclAs<ImplicitConceptSpecializationDecl>();
825  if (Record.readBool())
826  E->ConceptRef = Record.readConceptReference();
827  E->Satisfaction = E->isValueDependent() ? nullptr :
828  ASTConstraintSatisfaction::Create(Record.getContext(),
829  readConstraintSatisfaction(Record));
830 }
831 
832 static concepts::Requirement::SubstitutionDiagnostic *
833 readSubstitutionDiagnostic(ASTRecordReader &Record) {
834  std::string SubstitutedEntity = Record.readString();
835  SourceLocation DiagLoc = Record.readSourceLocation();
836  std::string DiagMessage = Record.readString();
837  return new (Record.getContext())
838  concepts::Requirement::SubstitutionDiagnostic{SubstitutedEntity, DiagLoc,
839  DiagMessage};
840 }
841 
842 void ASTStmtReader::VisitRequiresExpr(RequiresExpr *E) {
843  VisitExpr(E);
844  unsigned NumLocalParameters = Record.readInt();
845  unsigned NumRequirements = Record.readInt();
846  E->RequiresExprBits.RequiresKWLoc = Record.readSourceLocation();
847  E->RequiresExprBits.IsSatisfied = Record.readInt();
848  E->Body = Record.readDeclAs<RequiresExprBodyDecl>();
849  llvm::SmallVector<ParmVarDecl *, 4> LocalParameters;
850  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumLocalParameters; ++i)
851  LocalParameters.push_back(cast<ParmVarDecl>(Record.readDecl()));
852  std::copy(LocalParameters.begin(), LocalParameters.end(),
853  E->getTrailingObjects<ParmVarDecl *>());
854  llvm::SmallVector<concepts::Requirement *, 4> Requirements;
855  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumRequirements; ++i) {
856  auto RK =
857  static_cast<concepts::Requirement::RequirementKind>(Record.readInt());
858  concepts::Requirement *R = nullptr;
859  switch (RK) {
860  case concepts::Requirement::RK_Type: {
861  auto Status =
862  static_cast<concepts::TypeRequirement::SatisfactionStatus>(
863  Record.readInt());
864  if (Status == concepts::TypeRequirement::SS_SubstitutionFailure)
865  R = new (Record.getContext())
866  concepts::TypeRequirement(readSubstitutionDiagnostic(Record));
867  else
868  R = new (Record.getContext())
869  concepts::TypeRequirement(Record.readTypeSourceInfo());
870  } break;
871  case concepts::Requirement::RK_Simple:
872  case concepts::Requirement::RK_Compound: {
873  auto Status =
874  static_cast<concepts::ExprRequirement::SatisfactionStatus>(
875  Record.readInt());
876  llvm::PointerUnion<concepts::Requirement::SubstitutionDiagnostic *,
877  Expr *> E;
878  if (Status == concepts::ExprRequirement::SS_ExprSubstitutionFailure) {
879  E = readSubstitutionDiagnostic(Record);
880  } else
881  E = Record.readExpr();
882 
883  std::optional<concepts::ExprRequirement::ReturnTypeRequirement> Req;
884  ConceptSpecializationExpr *SubstitutedConstraintExpr = nullptr;
885  SourceLocation NoexceptLoc;
886  if (RK == concepts::Requirement::RK_Simple) {
887  Req.emplace();
888  } else {
889  NoexceptLoc = Record.readSourceLocation();
890  switch (/* returnTypeRequirementKind */Record.readInt()) {
891  case 0:
892  // No return type requirement.
893  Req.emplace();
894  break;
895  case 1: {
896  // type-constraint
897  TemplateParameterList *TPL = Record.readTemplateParameterList();
898  if (Status >=
899  concepts::ExprRequirement::SS_ConstraintsNotSatisfied)
900  SubstitutedConstraintExpr =
901  cast<ConceptSpecializationExpr>(Record.readExpr());
902  Req.emplace(TPL);
903  } break;
904  case 2:
905  // Substitution failure
906  Req.emplace(readSubstitutionDiagnostic(Record));
907  break;
908  }
909  }
910  if (Expr *Ex = E.dyn_cast<Expr *>())
911  R = new (Record.getContext()) concepts::ExprRequirement(
912  Ex, RK == concepts::Requirement::RK_Simple, NoexceptLoc,
913  std::move(*Req), Status, SubstitutedConstraintExpr);
914  else
915  R = new (Record.getContext()) concepts::ExprRequirement(
916  E.get<concepts::Requirement::SubstitutionDiagnostic *>(),
917  RK == concepts::Requirement::RK_Simple, NoexceptLoc,
918  std::move(*Req));
919  } break;
920  case concepts::Requirement::RK_Nested: {
921  bool HasInvalidConstraint = Record.readInt();
922  if (HasInvalidConstraint) {
923  std::string InvalidConstraint = Record.readString();
924  char *InvalidConstraintBuf =
925  new (Record.getContext()) char[InvalidConstraint.size()];
926  std::copy(InvalidConstraint.begin(), InvalidConstraint.end(),
927  InvalidConstraintBuf);
928  R = new (Record.getContext()) concepts::NestedRequirement(
929  Record.getContext(),
930  StringRef(InvalidConstraintBuf, InvalidConstraint.size()),
931  readConstraintSatisfaction(Record));
932  break;
933  }
934  Expr *E = Record.readExpr();
935  if (E->isInstantiationDependent())
936  R = new (Record.getContext()) concepts::NestedRequirement(E);
937  else
938  R = new (Record.getContext())
939  concepts::NestedRequirement(Record.getContext(), E,
940  readConstraintSatisfaction(Record));
941  } break;
942  }
943  if (!R)
944  continue;
945  Requirements.push_back(R);
946  }
947  std::copy(Requirements.begin(), Requirements.end(),
948  E->getTrailingObjects<concepts::Requirement *>());
949  E->LParenLoc = Record.readSourceLocation();
950  E->RParenLoc = Record.readSourceLocation();
951  E->RBraceLoc = Record.readSourceLocation();
952 }

980 void ASTStmtReader::VisitOMPArrayShapingExpr(OMPArrayShapingExpr *E) {

996 void ASTStmtReader::VisitOMPIteratorExpr(OMPIteratorExpr *E) {
997  VisitExpr(E);
998  unsigned NumIters = Record.readInt();
999  E->setIteratorKwLoc(readSourceLocation());
1000  E->setLParenLoc(readSourceLocation());
1001  E->setRParenLoc(readSourceLocation());
1002  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumIters; ++I) {
1003  E->setIteratorDeclaration(I, Record.readDeclRef());
1004  E->setAssignmentLoc(I, readSourceLocation());
1005  Expr *Begin = Record.readSubExpr();
1006  Expr *End = Record.readSubExpr();
1007  Expr *Step = Record.readSubExpr();
1008  SourceLocation ColonLoc = readSourceLocation();
1009  SourceLocation SecColonLoc;
1010  if (Step)
1011  SecColonLoc = readSourceLocation();
1012  E->setIteratorRange(I, Begin, ColonLoc, End, SecColonLoc, Step);
1013  // Deserialize helpers
1014  OMPIteratorHelperData HD;
1015  HD.CounterVD = cast_or_null<VarDecl>(Record.readDeclRef());
1016  HD.Upper = Record.readSubExpr();
1017  HD.Update = Record.readSubExpr();
1018  HD.CounterUpdate = Record.readSubExpr();
1019  E->setHelper(I, HD);
1020  }
1021 }

1023 void ASTStmtReader::VisitCallExpr(CallExpr *E) {
1024  VisitExpr(E);

1029  static_cast<CallExpr::ADLCallKind>(CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit()));
1030  bool HasFPFeatures = CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit();

1032  E->setRParenLoc(readSourceLocation());

1035  E->setArg(I, Record.readSubExpr());

1046 void ASTStmtReader::VisitMemberExpr(MemberExpr *E) {
1047  VisitExpr(E);
1048 
1049  CurrentUnpackingBits.emplace(Record.readInt());
1050  bool HasQualifier = CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit();
1051  bool HasFoundDecl = CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit();
1052  bool HasTemplateInfo = CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit();
1053  unsigned NumTemplateArgs = Record.readInt();
1054 
1055  E->Base = Record.readSubExpr();
1056  E->MemberDecl = Record.readDeclAs<ValueDecl>();
1057  E->MemberDNLoc = Record.readDeclarationNameLoc(E->MemberDecl->getDeclName());
1058  E->MemberLoc = Record.readSourceLocation();
1059  E->MemberExprBits.IsArrow = CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit();
1060  E->MemberExprBits.HasQualifier = HasQualifier;
1061  E->MemberExprBits.HasFoundDecl = HasFoundDecl;
1062  E->MemberExprBits.HasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo = HasTemplateInfo;
1063  E->MemberExprBits.HadMultipleCandidates = CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit();
1064  E->MemberExprBits.NonOdrUseReason =
1065  CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBits(/*Width=*/2);
1066  E->MemberExprBits.OperatorLoc = Record.readSourceLocation();
1067 
1068  if (HasQualifier)
1069  new (E->getTrailingObjects<NestedNameSpecifierLoc>())
1070  NestedNameSpecifierLoc(Record.readNestedNameSpecifierLoc());
1071 
1072  if (HasFoundDecl) {
1073  auto *FoundD = Record.readDeclAs<NamedDecl>();
1074  auto AS = (AccessSpecifier)CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBits(/*Width=*/2);
1075  *E->getTrailingObjects<DeclAccessPair>() = DeclAccessPair::make(FoundD, AS);
1076  }
1077 
1078  if (HasTemplateInfo)
1079  ReadTemplateKWAndArgsInfo(
1080  *E->getTrailingObjects<ASTTemplateKWAndArgsInfo>(),
1081  E->getTrailingObjects<TemplateArgumentLoc>(), NumTemplateArgs);
1082 }

1106 void ASTStmtReader::VisitCastExpr(CastExpr *E) {
1107  VisitExpr(E);
1108  unsigned NumBaseSpecs = Record.readInt();
1109  assert(NumBaseSpecs == E->path_size());
1110 
1111  CurrentUnpackingBits.emplace(Record.readInt());
1112  E->setCastKind((CastKind)CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBits(/*Width=*/7));
1113  unsigned HasFPFeatures = CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit();
1114  assert(E->hasStoredFPFeatures() == HasFPFeatures);
1115 
1116  E->setSubExpr(Record.readSubExpr());
1117 
1118  CastExpr::path_iterator BaseI = E->path_begin();
1119  while (NumBaseSpecs--) {
1120  auto *BaseSpec = new (Record.getContext()) CXXBaseSpecifier;
1121  *BaseSpec = Record.readCXXBaseSpecifier();
1122  *BaseI++ = BaseSpec;
1123  }
1124  if (HasFPFeatures)
1125  *E->getTrailingFPFeatures() =
1126  FPOptionsOverride::getFromOpaqueInt(Record.readInt());
1127 }

1202 void ASTStmtReader::VisitInitListExpr(InitListExpr *E) {
1203  VisitExpr(E);
1204  if (auto *SyntForm = cast_or_null<InitListExpr>(Record.readSubStmt()))
1205  E->setSyntacticForm(SyntForm);
1206  E->setLBraceLoc(readSourceLocation());
1207  E->setRBraceLoc(readSourceLocation());
1208  bool isArrayFiller = Record.readInt();
1209  Expr *filler = nullptr;
1210  if (isArrayFiller) {
1211  filler = Record.readSubExpr();
1212  E->ArrayFillerOrUnionFieldInit = filler;
1213  } else
1214  E->ArrayFillerOrUnionFieldInit = readDeclAs<FieldDecl>();
1215  E->sawArrayRangeDesignator(Record.readInt());
1216  unsigned NumInits = Record.readInt();
1217  E->reserveInits(Record.getContext(), NumInits);
1218  if (isArrayFiller) {
1219  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumInits; ++I) {
1220  Expr *init = Record.readSubExpr();
1221  E->updateInit(Record.getContext(), I, init ? init : filler);
1222  }
1223  } else {
1224  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumInits; ++I)
1225  E->updateInit(Record.getContext(), I, Record.readSubExpr());
1226  }
1227 }

1229 void ASTStmtReader::VisitDesignatedInitExpr(DesignatedInitExpr *E) {
1230  using Designator = DesignatedInitExpr::Designator;
1231 
1232  VisitExpr(E);
1233  unsigned NumSubExprs = Record.readInt();
1234  assert(NumSubExprs == E->getNumSubExprs() && "Wrong number of subexprs");
1235  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumSubExprs; ++I)
1236  E->setSubExpr(I, Record.readSubExpr());
1237  E->setEqualOrColonLoc(readSourceLocation());
1238  E->setGNUSyntax(Record.readInt());
1239 
1240  SmallVector<Designator, 4> Designators;
1241  while (Record.getIdx() < Record.size()) {
1242  switch ((DesignatorTypes)Record.readInt()) {
1243  case DESIG_FIELD_DECL: {
1244  auto *Field = readDeclAs<FieldDecl>();
1245  SourceLocation DotLoc = readSourceLocation();
1246  SourceLocation FieldLoc = readSourceLocation();
1247  Designators.push_back(Designator::CreateFieldDesignator(
1248  Field->getIdentifier(), DotLoc, FieldLoc));
1249  Designators.back().setFieldDecl(Field);
1250  break;
1251  }
1252 
1253  case DESIG_FIELD_NAME: {
1254  const IdentifierInfo *Name = Record.readIdentifier();
1255  SourceLocation DotLoc = readSourceLocation();
1256  SourceLocation FieldLoc = readSourceLocation();
1257  Designators.push_back(Designator::CreateFieldDesignator(Name, DotLoc,
1258  FieldLoc));
1259  break;
1260  }
1261 
1262  case DESIG_ARRAY: {
1263  unsigned Index = Record.readInt();
1264  SourceLocation LBracketLoc = readSourceLocation();
1265  SourceLocation RBracketLoc = readSourceLocation();
1266  Designators.push_back(Designator::CreateArrayDesignator(Index,
1267  LBracketLoc,
1268  RBracketLoc));
1269  break;
1270  }
1271 
1272  case DESIG_ARRAY_RANGE: {
1273  unsigned Index = Record.readInt();
1274  SourceLocation LBracketLoc = readSourceLocation();
1275  SourceLocation EllipsisLoc = readSourceLocation();
1276  SourceLocation RBracketLoc = readSourceLocation();
1277  Designators.push_back(Designator::CreateArrayRangeDesignator(
1278  Index, LBracketLoc, EllipsisLoc, RBracketLoc));
1279  break;
1280  }
1281  }
1282  }
1283  E->setDesignators(Record.getContext(),
1284  Designators.data(), Designators.size());
1285 }

1382 void ASTStmtReader::VisitGenericSelectionExpr(GenericSelectionExpr *E) {
1383  VisitExpr(E);
1384 
1385  unsigned NumAssocs = Record.readInt();
1386  assert(NumAssocs == E->getNumAssocs() && "Wrong NumAssocs!");
1387  E->IsExprPredicate = Record.readInt();
1388  E->ResultIndex = Record.readInt();
1389  E->GenericSelectionExprBits.GenericLoc = readSourceLocation();
1390  E->DefaultLoc = readSourceLocation();
1391  E->RParenLoc = readSourceLocation();
1392 
1393  Stmt **Stmts = E->getTrailingObjects<Stmt *>();
1394  // Add 1 to account for the controlling expression which is the first
1395  // expression in the trailing array of Stmt *. This is not needed for
1396  // the trailing array of TypeSourceInfo *.
1397  for (unsigned I = 0, N = NumAssocs + 1; I < N; ++I)
1398  Stmts[I] = Record.readSubExpr();
1399 
1400  TypeSourceInfo **TSIs = E->getTrailingObjects<TypeSourceInfo *>();
1401  for (unsigned I = 0, N = NumAssocs; I < N; ++I)
1402  TSIs[I] = readTypeSourceInfo();
1403 }

1405 void ASTStmtReader::VisitPseudoObjectExpr(PseudoObjectExpr *E) {
1406  VisitExpr(E);
1407  unsigned numSemanticExprs = Record.readInt();
1408  assert(numSemanticExprs + 1 == E->PseudoObjectExprBits.NumSubExprs);
1409  E->PseudoObjectExprBits.ResultIndex = Record.readInt();
1410 
1411  // Read the syntactic expression.
1412  E->getSubExprsBuffer()[0] = Record.readSubExpr();
1413 
1414  // Read all the semantic expressions.
1415  for (unsigned i = 0; i != numSemanticExprs; ++i) {
1416  Expr *subExpr = Record.readSubExpr();
1417  E->getSubExprsBuffer()[i+1] = subExpr;
1418  }
1419 }

1478  E->Range = readSourceRange();

1513 void ASTStmtReader::VisitObjCPropertyRefExpr(ObjCPropertyRefExpr *E) {
1514  VisitExpr(E);
1515  unsigned MethodRefFlags = Record.readInt();
1516  bool Implicit = Record.readInt() != 0;
1517  if (Implicit) {
1518  auto *Getter = readDeclAs<ObjCMethodDecl>();
1519  auto *Setter = readDeclAs<ObjCMethodDecl>();
1520  E->setImplicitProperty(Getter, Setter, MethodRefFlags);
1521  } else {
1522  E->setExplicitProperty(readDeclAs<ObjCPropertyDecl>(), MethodRefFlags);
1523  }
1524  E->setLocation(readSourceLocation());
1525  E->setReceiverLocation(readSourceLocation());
1526  switch (Record.readInt()) {
1527  case 0:
1528  E->setBase(Record.readSubExpr());
1529  break;
1530  case 1:
1531  E->setSuperReceiver(Record.readType());
1532  break;
1533  case 2:
1534  E->setClassReceiver(readDeclAs<ObjCInterfaceDecl>());
1535  break;
1536  }
1537 }

1548 void ASTStmtReader::VisitObjCMessageExpr(ObjCMessageExpr *E) {
1549  VisitExpr(E);
1550  assert(Record.peekInt() == E->getNumArgs());
1551  Record.skipInts(1);
1552  unsigned NumStoredSelLocs = Record.readInt();
1553  E->SelLocsKind = Record.readInt();
1554  E->setDelegateInitCall(Record.readInt());
1555  E->IsImplicit = Record.readInt();
1556  auto Kind = static_cast<ObjCMessageExpr::ReceiverKind>(Record.readInt());
1557  switch (Kind) {
1558  case ObjCMessageExpr::Instance:
1559  E->setInstanceReceiver(Record.readSubExpr());
1560  break;
1561 
1562  case ObjCMessageExpr::Class:
1563  E->setClassReceiver(readTypeSourceInfo());
1564  break;
1565 
1566  case ObjCMessageExpr::SuperClass:
1567  case ObjCMessageExpr::SuperInstance: {
1568  QualType T = Record.readType();
1569  SourceLocation SuperLoc = readSourceLocation();
1570  E->setSuper(SuperLoc, T, Kind == ObjCMessageExpr::SuperInstance);
1571  break;
1572  }
1573  }
1574 
1575  assert(Kind == E->getReceiverKind());
1576 
1577  if (Record.readInt())
1578  E->setMethodDecl(readDeclAs<ObjCMethodDecl>());
1579  else
1580  E->setSelector(Record.readSelector());
1581 
1582  E->LBracLoc = readSourceLocation();
1583  E->RBracLoc = readSourceLocation();
1584 
1585  for (unsigned I = 0, N = E->getNumArgs(); I != N; ++I)
1586  E->setArg(I, Record.readSubExpr());
1587 
1588  SourceLocation *Locs = E->getStoredSelLocs();
1589  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumStoredSelLocs; ++I)
1590  Locs[I] = readSourceLocation();
1591 }

1765  E->LambdaExprBits.ExplicitResultType = Record.readInt();
1766  E->ClosingBrace = readSourceLocation();
1767 
1768  // Read capture initializers.
1769  for (LambdaExpr::capture_init_iterator C = E->capture_init_begin(),
1770  CEnd = E->capture_init_end();
1771  C != CEnd; ++C)
1772  *C = Record.readSubExpr();
1773 
1774  // The body will be lazily deserialized when needed from the call operator
1775  // declaration.
1776 }

1918 void ASTStmtReader::VisitCXXNewExpr(CXXNewExpr *E) {
1919  VisitExpr(E);
1920 
1921  bool IsArray = Record.readInt();
1922  bool HasInit = Record.readInt();
1923  unsigned NumPlacementArgs = Record.readInt();
1924  bool IsParenTypeId = Record.readInt();
1925 
1926  E->CXXNewExprBits.IsGlobalNew = Record.readInt();
1927  E->CXXNewExprBits.ShouldPassAlignment = Record.readInt();
1928  E->CXXNewExprBits.UsualArrayDeleteWantsSize = Record.readInt();
1929  E->CXXNewExprBits.HasInitializer = Record.readInt();
1930  E->CXXNewExprBits.StoredInitializationStyle = Record.readInt();
1931 
1932  assert((IsArray == E->isArray()) && "Wrong IsArray!");
1933  assert((HasInit == E->hasInitializer()) && "Wrong HasInit!");
1934  assert((NumPlacementArgs == E->getNumPlacementArgs()) &&
1935  "Wrong NumPlacementArgs!");
1936  assert((IsParenTypeId == E->isParenTypeId()) && "Wrong IsParenTypeId!");
1937  (void)IsArray;
1938  (void)HasInit;
1939  (void)NumPlacementArgs;
1940 
1941  E->setOperatorNew(readDeclAs<FunctionDecl>());
1942  E->setOperatorDelete(readDeclAs<FunctionDecl>());
1943  E->AllocatedTypeInfo = readTypeSourceInfo();
1944  if (IsParenTypeId)
1945  E->getTrailingObjects<SourceRange>()[0] = readSourceRange();
1946  E->Range = readSourceRange();
1947  E->DirectInitRange = readSourceRange();
1948 
1949  // Install all the subexpressions.
1950  for (CXXNewExpr::raw_arg_iterator I = E->raw_arg_begin(),
1951  N = E->raw_arg_end();
1952  I != N; ++I)
1953  *I = Record.readSubStmt();
1954 }

1985 void ASTStmtReader::VisitExprWithCleanups(ExprWithCleanups *E) {
1986  VisitExpr(E);
1987 
1988  unsigned NumObjects = Record.readInt();
1989  assert(NumObjects == E->getNumObjects());
1990  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumObjects; ++i) {
1991  unsigned CleanupKind = Record.readInt();
1992  ExprWithCleanups::CleanupObject Obj;
1993  if (CleanupKind == COK_Block)
1994  Obj = readDeclAs<BlockDecl>();
1995  else if (CleanupKind == COK_CompoundLiteral)
1996  Obj = cast<CompoundLiteralExpr>(Record.readSubExpr());
1997  else
1998  llvm_unreachable("unexpected cleanup object type");
1999  E->getTrailingObjects<ExprWithCleanups::CleanupObject>()[i] = Obj;
2000  }
2001 
2002  E->ExprWithCleanupsBits.CleanupsHaveSideEffects = Record.readInt();
2003  E->SubExpr = Record.readSubExpr();
2004 }

2006 void ASTStmtReader::VisitCXXDependentScopeMemberExpr(
2007  CXXDependentScopeMemberExpr *E) {
2008  VisitExpr(E);
2009 
2010  unsigned NumTemplateArgs = Record.readInt();
2011  CurrentUnpackingBits.emplace(Record.readInt());
2012  bool HasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo = CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit();
2013  bool HasFirstQualifierFoundInScope = CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit();
2014 
2015  assert((HasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo == E->hasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo()) &&
2016  "Wrong HasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo!");
2017  assert(
2018  (HasFirstQualifierFoundInScope == E->hasFirstQualifierFoundInScope()) &&
2019  "Wrong HasFirstQualifierFoundInScope!");
2020 
2021  if (HasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo)
2022  ReadTemplateKWAndArgsInfo(
2023  *E->getTrailingObjects<ASTTemplateKWAndArgsInfo>(),
2024  E->getTrailingObjects<TemplateArgumentLoc>(), NumTemplateArgs);
2025 
2026  assert((NumTemplateArgs == E->getNumTemplateArgs()) &&
2027  "Wrong NumTemplateArgs!");
2028 
2029  E->CXXDependentScopeMemberExprBits.IsArrow =
2030  CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit();
2031 
2032  E->BaseType = Record.readType();
2033  E->QualifierLoc = Record.readNestedNameSpecifierLoc();
2034  // not ImplicitAccess
2035  if (CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit())
2036  E->Base = Record.readSubExpr();
2037  else
2038  E->Base = nullptr;
2039 
2040  E->CXXDependentScopeMemberExprBits.OperatorLoc = readSourceLocation();
2041 
2042  if (HasFirstQualifierFoundInScope)
2043  *E->getTrailingObjects<NamedDecl *>() = readDeclAs<NamedDecl>();
2044 
2045  E->MemberNameInfo = Record.readDeclarationNameInfo();
2046 }

2063 ASTStmtReader::VisitCXXUnresolvedConstructExpr(CXXUnresolvedConstructExpr *E) {
2064  VisitExpr(E);

2066  "Read wrong record during creation ?");
2067  Record.skipInts(1);

2069  E->setArg(I, Record.readSubExpr());

2076 void ASTStmtReader::VisitOverloadExpr(OverloadExpr *E) {
2077  VisitExpr(E);
2078 
2079  unsigned NumResults = Record.readInt();
2080  CurrentUnpackingBits.emplace(Record.readInt());
2081  bool HasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo = CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit();
2082  assert((E->getNumDecls() == NumResults) && "Wrong NumResults!");
2083  assert((E->hasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo() == HasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo) &&
2084  "Wrong HasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo!");
2085 
2086  if (HasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo) {
2087  unsigned NumTemplateArgs = Record.readInt();
2088  ReadTemplateKWAndArgsInfo(*E->getTrailingASTTemplateKWAndArgsInfo(),
2089  E->getTrailingTemplateArgumentLoc(),
2090  NumTemplateArgs);
2091  assert((E->getNumTemplateArgs() == NumTemplateArgs) &&
2092  "Wrong NumTemplateArgs!");
2093  }
2094 
2095  UnresolvedSet<8> Decls;
2096  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumResults; ++I) {
2097  auto *D = readDeclAs<NamedDecl>();
2098  auto AS = (AccessSpecifier)Record.readInt();
2099  Decls.addDecl(D, AS);
2100  }
2101 
2102  DeclAccessPair *Results = E->getTrailingResults();
2103  UnresolvedSetIterator Iter = Decls.begin();
2104  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumResults; ++I) {
2105  Results[I] = (Iter + I).getPair();
2106  }
2107 
2108  E->NameInfo = Record.readDeclarationNameInfo();
2109  E->QualifierLoc = Record.readNestedNameSpecifierLoc();
2110 }

2117 
2118  if (/*!isImplicitAccess=*/CurrentUnpackingBits->getNextBit())
2119  E->Base = Record.readSubExpr();
2120  else
2121  E->Base = nullptr;
2122 
2123  E->OperatorLoc = readSourceLocation();
2124

2345  E->Operand = readTypeSourceInfo();
2346  else
2347  E->Operand = Record.readSubExpr();
2348 }

2837 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2838 // ASTReader Implementation
2839 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2840 
2841 Stmt *ASTReader::ReadStmt(ModuleFile &F) {
2842  switch (ReadingKind) {
2843  case Read_None:
2844  llvm_unreachable("should not call this when not reading anything");
2845  case Read_Decl:
2846  case Read_Type:
2847  return ReadStmtFromStream(F);
2848  case Read_Stmt:
2849  return ReadSubStmt();
2850  }
2851 
2852  llvm_unreachable("ReadingKind not set ?");
2853 }
2854 
2855 Expr *ASTReader::ReadExpr(ModuleFile &F) {
2856  return cast_or_null<Expr>(ReadStmt(F));
2857 }
2858 
2859 Expr *ASTReader::ReadSubExpr() {
2860  return cast_or_null<Expr>(ReadSubStmt());
2861 }
2862 
2863 // Within the bitstream, expressions are stored in Reverse Polish
2864 // Notation, with each of the subexpressions preceding the
2865 // expression they are stored in. Subexpressions are stored from last to first.
2866 // To evaluate expressions, we continue reading expressions and placing them on
2867 // the stack, with expressions having operands removing those operands from the
2868 // stack. Evaluation terminates when we see a STMT_STOP record, and
2869 // the single remaining expression on the stack is our result.
2870 Stmt *ASTReader::ReadStmtFromStream(ModuleFile &F) {
2871  ReadingKindTracker ReadingKind(Read_Stmt, *this);
2872  llvm::BitstreamCursor &Cursor = F.DeclsCursor;
2873 
2874  // Map of offset to previously deserialized stmt. The offset points
2875  // just after the stmt record.
2876  llvm::DenseMap<uint64_t, Stmt *> StmtEntries;
2877 
2878 #ifndef NDEBUG
2879  unsigned PrevNumStmts = StmtStack.size();
2880 #endif
2881 
2882  ASTRecordReader Record(*this, F);
2883  ASTStmtReader Reader(Record, Cursor);
2884  Stmt::EmptyShell Empty;
2885 
2886  while (true) {
2887  llvm::Expected<llvm::BitstreamEntry> MaybeEntry =
2888  Cursor.advanceSkippingSubblocks();
2889  if (!MaybeEntry) {
2890  Error(toString(MaybeEntry.takeError()));
2891  return nullptr;
2892  }
2893  llvm::BitstreamEntry Entry = MaybeEntry.get();
2894 
2895  switch (Entry.Kind) {
2896  case llvm::BitstreamEntry::SubBlock: // Handled for us already.
2897  case llvm::BitstreamEntry::Error:
2898  Error("malformed block record in AST file");
2899  return nullptr;
2900  case llvm::BitstreamEntry::EndBlock:
2901  goto Done;
2902  case llvm::BitstreamEntry::Record:
2903  // The interesting case.
2904  break;
2905  }
2906 
2907  ASTContext &Context = getContext();
2908  Stmt *S = nullptr;
2909  bool Finished = false;
2910  bool IsStmtReference = false;
2911  Expected<unsigned> MaybeStmtCode = Record.readRecord(Cursor, Entry.ID);
2912  if (!MaybeStmtCode) {
2913  Error(toString(MaybeStmtCode.takeError()));
2914  return nullptr;
2915  }
2916  switch ((StmtCode)MaybeStmtCode.get()) {
2917  case STMT_STOP:
2918  Finished = true;
2919  break;
2920 
2921  case STMT_REF_PTR:
2922  IsStmtReference = true;
2923  assert(StmtEntries.contains(Record[0]) &&
2924  "No stmt was recorded for this offset reference!");
2925  S = StmtEntries[Record.readInt()];
2926  break;
2927 
2928  case STMT_NULL_PTR:
2929  S = nullptr;
2930  break;
2931 
2932  case STMT_NULL:
2933  S = new (Context) NullStmt(Empty);
2934  break;
2935 
2936  case STMT_COMPOUND: {
2937  unsigned NumStmts = Record[ASTStmtReader::NumStmtFields];
2938  bool HasFPFeatures = Record[ASTStmtReader::NumStmtFields + 1];
2939  S = CompoundStmt::CreateEmpty(Context, NumStmts, HasFPFeatures);
2940  break;
2941  }
2942 
2943  case STMT_CASE:
2944  S = CaseStmt::CreateEmpty(
2945  Context,
2946  /*CaseStmtIsGNURange*/ Record[ASTStmtReader::NumStmtFields + 3]);
2947  break;
2948 
2949  case STMT_DEFAULT:
2950  S = new (Context) DefaultStmt(Empty);
2951  break;
2952 
2953  case STMT_LABEL:
2954  S = new (Context) LabelStmt(Empty);
2955  break;
2956 
2957  case STMT_ATTRIBUTED:
2958  S = AttributedStmt::CreateEmpty(
2959  Context,
2960  /*NumAttrs*/Record[ASTStmtReader::NumStmtFields]);
2961  break;
2962 
2963  case STMT_IF: {
2964  BitsUnpacker IfStmtBits(Record[ASTStmtReader::NumStmtFields]);
2965  bool HasElse = IfStmtBits.getNextBit();

4162  S = new (Context) ArrayTypeTraitExpr(Empty);
4163  break;
4164 
4165  case EXPR_CXX_EXPRESSION_TRAIT:
4166  S = new (Context) ExpressionTraitExpr(Empty);
4167  break;

4171  break;

4174  S = new (Context) PackExpansionExpr(Empty);
4175  break;
4176 
4177  case EXPR_SIZEOF_PACK:

4179  Context,
4180  /*NumPartialArgs=*/Record[ASTStmtReader::NumExprFields]);
4181  break;
4182 
4183  case EXPR_PACK_INDEXING:
4184  S = PackIndexingExpr::CreateDeserialized(
4185  Context,
4186  /*TransformedExprs=*/Record[ASTStmtReader::NumExprFields]);
4187  break;

4191  break;

4195  break;

4199  Record[ASTStmtReader::NumExprFields]);
4200  break;
4201

4203  S = new (Context) MaterializeTemporaryExpr(Empty);
4204  break;
4205 
4206  case EXPR_CXX_FOLD:
4207  S = new (Context) CXXFoldExpr(Empty);
4208  break;
4209 
4210  case EXPR_CXX_PAREN_LIST_INIT:
4211  S = CXXParenListInitExpr::CreateEmpty(
4212  Context, /*numExprs=*/Record[ASTStmtReader::NumExprFields], Empty);
4213  break;
4214 
4215  case EXPR_OPAQUE_VALUE:
4216  S = new (Context) OpaqueValueExpr(Empty);
4217  break;
4218 
4219  case EXPR_CUDA_KERNEL_CALL: {
4220  auto NumArgs = Record[ASTStmtReader::NumExprFields];
4221  BitsUnpacker CallExprBits(Record[ASTStmtReader::NumExprFields + 1]);
4222  CallExprBits.advance(1);
4223  auto HasFPFeatures = CallExprBits.getNextBit();
4224  S = CUDAKernelCallExpr::CreateEmpty(Context, NumArgs, HasFPFeatures,
4225  Empty);
4226  break;
4227  }
4228 
4229  case EXPR_ASTYPE:
4230  S = new (Context) AsTypeExpr(Empty);
4231  break;
4232 
4233  case EXPR_PSEUDO_OBJECT: {
4234  unsigned numSemanticExprs = Record[ASTStmtReader::NumExprFields];
4235  S = PseudoObjectExpr::Create(Context, Empty, numSemanticExprs);
4236  break;
4237  }
4238 
4239  case EXPR_ATOMIC:
4240  S = new (Context) AtomicExpr(Empty);
4241  break;
4242 
4243  case EXPR_LAMBDA: {
4244  unsigned NumCaptures = Record[ASTStmtReader::NumExprFields];
4245  S = LambdaExpr::CreateDeserialized(Context, NumCaptures);
4246  break;
4247  }
4248 
4249  case STMT_COROUTINE_BODY: {
4250  unsigned NumParams = Record[ASTStmtReader::NumStmtFields];
4251  S = CoroutineBodyStmt::Create(Context, Empty, NumParams);
4252  break;
4253  }
4254 
4255  case STMT_CORETURN:
4256  S = new (Context) CoreturnStmt(Empty);
4257  break;
4258 
4259  case EXPR_COAWAIT:
4260  S = new (Context) CoawaitExpr(Empty);
4261  break;
4262 
4263  case EXPR_COYIELD:
4264  S = new (Context) CoyieldExpr(Empty);
4265  break;
4266 
4267  case EXPR_DEPENDENT_COAWAIT:
4268  S = new (Context) DependentCoawaitExpr(Empty);
4269  break;
4270 
4271  case EXPR_CONCEPT_SPECIALIZATION: {
4272  S = new (Context) ConceptSpecializationExpr(Empty);
4273  break;
4274  }
4275  case STMT_OPENACC_COMPUTE_CONSTRUCT: {
4276  unsigned NumClauses = Record[ASTStmtReader::NumStmtFields];
4277  S = OpenACCComputeConstruct::CreateEmpty(Context, NumClauses);
4278  break;
4279  }
4280  case EXPR_REQUIRES:
4281  unsigned numLocalParameters = Record[ASTStmtReader::NumExprFields];
4282  unsigned numRequirement = Record[ASTStmtReader::NumExprFields + 1];
4283  S = RequiresExpr::Create(Context, Empty, numLocalParameters,
4284  numRequirement);
4285  break;
4286  }
4287 
4288  // We hit a STMT_STOP, so we're done with this expression.
4289  if (Finished)
4290  break;
4291 
4292  ++NumStatementsRead;
4293 
4294  if (S && !IsStmtReference) {
4295  Reader.Visit(S);
4296  StmtEntries[Cursor.GetCurrentBitNo()] = S;
4297  }
4298 
4299  assert(Record.getIdx() == Record.size() &&
4300  "Invalid deserialization of statement");
4301  StmtStack.push_back(S);
4302  }
4303 Done:
4304  assert(StmtStack.size() > PrevNumStmts && "Read too many sub-stmts!");
4305  assert(StmtStack.size() == PrevNumStmts + 1 && "Extra expressions on stack!");
4306  return StmtStack.pop_back_val();
4307 }
